MOTION DOCKET

87-447. State v. Henderson.

Hamilton County, No. C-850557. This cause came on for further consideration upon appellant’s motion to stay his execution, now scheduled for January 26,1993, pending the final disposition by the Ohio courts of his federal constitutional claims raised in his application for delayed reconsideration, filed in the First District Court of Appeals. Upon consideration thereof,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that said motion to stay the execution be, and the same is hereby, granted, effective December 7, 1992.

Resnick, J., dissents.
